{{Top|leg}}
A '''Jedi shadow bomb''' was essentially a [[Proton torpedo/Legends|proton torpedo]] with the guidance package and propellant fuel replaced by packed [[Baradium/Legends|baradium]], the explosive material used in [[Thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonators]]. Instead of locking onto a target and firing the shadow bomb like a normal torpedo, the Jedi utilized the weapon with use of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] to propel the bomb into an enemy ship. The extra explosives stored within each missile vastly increased their individual destructive power; a pair of well-placed shadow bombs could cleave a [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[I'Friil Ma-Nat|corvette analog]] in half.

The tactic of using the Force to aim an explosive (not intended for this boosted use) to destroy the enemies of the light dates back at least to 9 ABY, when Luke Skywalker used his object moving powers to re-aim a torpedo.<ref name="Heir to the Empire">''[[Heir to the Empire]]''</ref> The shadow bomb was first developed during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]] as a countermeasure to the ability of the Yuuzhan Vong to detect and intercept normal proton torpedoes. Each Vong ship had [[Dovin basal|living gravity generators]] that could create miniature singularities to suck in laser fire and other forms of ordnance. Since proton torpedoes were primarily detected by the propellant trail they left behind, the Vong could sense them. However, they could not sense shadow bombs (for a while), making them very effective when used correctly.

Eventually, the Yuuzhan Vong learned to detect shadow bombs, much to the Jedi's relative disappointment, leading to their eventual abandonment in the latter stages of the war. However, they would see renewed use by the Jedi in the [[Battle of the Murgo Choke]] against the [[Killik/Legends|Killik]] nest ships and again throughout the [[Swarm War]], the [[Second Galactic Civil War]] and beyond. During the Second Galactic Civil war, it was used during the [[Battle of Kashyyyk (Second Galactic Civil War)|Battle of Kashyyyk]] by the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Lowbacca]] against the [[Anakin Solo (starship)|''Anakin Solo'']].

While an effective weapon, its use against Force-users is rather limited, as seen when [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina Solo]] was battling [[Ship (Sith Meditation Sphere)|Ship]], who used the Force to tear the bombs from her grasp to protect itself.

